hackathon-description-text: WarwickHACK is a hackathon where Programmers, Entrepreneurs, Designers and Developers come together to build, make and create. The event is a classic hackathon, where you have 24 hours to go crazy with your ideas! There will be prizes available for attendees who have the mostfor the most innovative, creative and different uses of sponsor APIs as well as prizes for entrepreneurship. More details will be coming soon!
hackathon-eligibility:
- 18 or older and be a student or have graduated in the current year
- Must have ID on hand to enter the event
hackathon-rules: In order to enter, you must be 18 or older and be a student or have graduated in the current year. You must able to present student ID to organisers upon entry to the event. Submissions must be created on the day for entry into the prize competition, but anything can be worked on during the event.
hackathon-description-header: 24 hour hackathon hosted at Warwick University
